  "description": [
    "FEBRUARY 19 83 Will Mi Garrison please give a place in the Liberator to the following which was refused insertion in the Christian Register c K w For tho Christian Register RELATION OF UNITARIANISM TO CASTE The Register in pleading guilty to the charge of the Liberator that it neglected to announce and to denounce the injustice practised towards Mrs Webb by the keeper of the Marlboro Hotel two years ago suggests the following circumstances apparently by way of extenuation 1 The seven other religious papers of Boston did the same thing 2 ln our very spare summary of secular news we probably thought the occurrence not of sufficient public interest to be noticed 3 1 It is unhappily no rare event for our colored friends to be treated with indignity Our silence is by no means approbation Upon each of these points I ask the privilege of making a few words of comment 1 If the Register neither pretends to possess nor aspires to attain in regard to the education of the public in good manners good morals and true religion all of which are concerned in this matter any high er orjuster or more liberal ideas than the"
